	* Attic/main.c, Attic/pkgdir.c, Attic/pkgdir.h, Attic/pkgset-load.h, Attic/poldek.pod, pkgset-load.c:
	- added 'type' source option
	- cleanups

	* Attic/pkgdir_load_dir.c: - 'hdlist' load fixed

	* vfile/vfile.c:
	- vfile_fetcha() fix: mkdir destdir if it doesn't exists

	* vfile/vhttp/Attic/Makefile.in: - added by mistake

2002-04-06  Pawe³ Gajda  <mis@pld.org.pl>

	* pkgset-load.c, Attic/main.c: - cosmetics

	* shell/Attic/desc.c, po/pl.po, Attic/main.c, Attic/pkgdir.h, Attic/pkgdir_load_dir.c, Attic/pkgset-load.h, pkg.c, pkg.h, pkgfetch.c, pkgfl.c, pkgset-load.c:
	- added support for header list files as sources (aka hdlist, aka tocfile);
	  now RH and propably other RPM based distributions are usable to poldek, i.e:

	  $ poldek --shdl=ftp://ftp.redhat.com/pub/redhat/redhat-7.2-en/os/i386/RedHat/base/hdlist \
	    --shdl=ftp://ftp.redhat.com/pub/redhat/redhat-7.2-en/os/i386/RedHat/base/hdlist2 \
	    -P ftp://ftp.redhat.com/pub/redhat/redhat-7.2-en/os/i386/RedHat/RPMS/

	  works :-) However RH's hdlist's have removed almost all file list from
	  headers.

	* vfile/vhttp/Attic/.cvsignore, vfile/vhttp/Attic/Makefile.am, vfile/vhttp/Attic/Makefile.in, vfile/vhttp/Attic/http.c, vfile/vhttp/Attic/http.h, vfile/vhttp/Attic/req.txt, vfile/vhttp/Attic/test_vhttp.c, vfile/vhttp/Attic/vhttp.c, vfile/vhttp/Attic/vhttp.h, vfile/Attic/vfvhttp.c, vfile/vfile.c, vfile/Makefile.am, Attic/NEWS, Attic/homepage.sgml.in, Attic/poldek.pod, Makefile.am, Makefile.extra, configure.in, poldek-suse.spec.in, poldek.spec.in:
	- added HTTP client; curl module not compiled by default

	* test_patch.sh: - fix

	* po/POTFILES.in, po/pl.po: - $ make update-po

	* shell/Attic/shell.c:
	- warn/raise error on ambiguous strcmp() matching

	* pkgset-install.c: - skip packages installed in equal version

	* pkgset-load.c: - SIGSEV killed

